medicines.name: ginger root
medicines.description: Ginger root is a popular medicinal and culinary herb known for its spicy, pungent flavor and numerous health benefits. It is widely used in traditional medicine and modern health supplements.

medicines.name: Herbal Liver Detox
medicines.description:
Herbal Liver Detox is a combination of natural plant extracts that promote healthy liver function and detoxification. It supports the liver’s natural ability to remove toxins, improves digestion, and protects liver cells from damage caused by alcohol, medications, or fatty liver disease.

It is non-prescription and widely used as a daily detox supplement.

medicines.name: Echinacea
medicines.dosage: Take 1 capsule twice a day after meals
medicines.description:
Echinacea is a herbal immune-boosting supplement derived from the Echinacea plant (commonly Echinacea purpurea or Echinacea angustifolia). Traditionally used in natural medicine, it helps to prevent and treat the common cold, flu, and respiratory infections.

It is also believed to support general immune function and reduce the duration of infections when taken at the first sign of illness.

medicines.name: Tylenol Extra Strenght
medicines.description: Tylenol Extra Strength is a widely used over-the-counter medication containing 500 mg of acetaminophen per caplet. It is designed to provide temporary relief from minor aches and pains and to reduce fever.

medicines.name: paracetamol
medicines.description: Amoxicillin is a broad-spectrum antibiotic in the penicillin family. It treats bacterial infections in various parts of the body, including ear infections, throat infections (pharyngitis/tonsillitis), sinusitis, chest infections (bronchitis, pneumonia), urinary tract infections, and some gastrointestinal infections (e.g., H. pylori eradication when combined with other medications). It works by interfering with the synthesis of the bacterial cell wall, causing the bacteria to rupture. Patients must complete the full prescribed course (typically 7–14 days, depending on the infection) even if they feel better before the dose is finished. Suddenly stopping the medication can allow the infection to return and may promote antibiotic resistance. Common side effects include nausea, diarrhea, and allergic reactions (rash or, rarely, anaphylaxis).

medicines.name: Omeprazole
medicines.description: Omeprazole is a proton pump inhibitor (PPI) that decreases the amount of acid produced in the stomach. It is used to treat conditions such as gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), peptic ulcers, Zollinger–Ellison syndrome (a condition where the stomach produces too much acid), and erosive esophagitis. By blocking the enzyme responsible for acid secretion (H⁺/K⁺-ATPase) in gastric parietal cells, omeprazole raises the pH of the stomach, allowing ulcers to heal and relieving symptoms like heartburn and indigestion. It is usually taken once daily, 30 minutes before a meal, and should not be crushed or chewed—capsules should be swallowed whole or the contents sprinkled on a small amount of applesauce if necessary. Long-term use may lead to decreased absorption of certain nutrients (like vitamin B₁₂, magnesium) and increased risk of bone fractures, so extended therapy should be supervised by a physician.

medicines.name: Metformin
medicines.description: Metformin is an oral antidiabetic medication used primarily for managing type 2 diabetes mellitus. It belongs to the biguanide class and works by reducing hepatic glucose production, decreasing intestinal absorption of glucose, and improving insulin sensitivity in peripheral tissues. This helps lower blood glucose levels and improves glycemic control. Metformin is often the first-line therapy for type 2 diabetics, especially in overweight or obese patients, because it does not typically cause weight gain and may even promote slight weight loss. Common side effects include gastrointestinal disturbances (nausea, diarrhea, abdominal discomfort), which can often be minimized by taking the drug with meals and the gradual titration of dose. In rare cases, it can cause lactic acidosis, especially in patients with renal impairment or other contraindications, so kidney function should be monitored periodically.

medicines.name: Atorvastatin
medicines.description: Atorvastatin is a statin medication used to lower elevated levels of cholesterol and triglycerides in the blood. It primarily reduces LDL cholesterol (“bad cholesterol”) and modestly raises HDL cholesterol (“good cholesterol”), helping prevent cardiovascular events such as heart attacks and strokes.

medicines.name: Ibuprofen
medicines.description: Ibuprofen belongs to the Non-Steroidal Anti-Inflammatory Drug (NSAID) class. It helps reduce inflammation, relieve pain, and lower fever. Common uses include treating headaches, menstrual cramps, toothaches, muscle aches, arthritis, and other inflammatory conditions. It works by blocking the enzymes (COX-1 and COX-2) that produce prostaglandins, which are responsible for pain and swelling. Ibuprofen should be taken with food or milk to minimize the risk of stomach irritation or ulcers. People with a history of peptic ulcers, kidney disease, or certain cardiovascular conditions should use it under medical supervision.

medicines.name: Cetirizine
medicines.description: Cetirizine is an antihistamine used to relieve allergy symptoms such as sneezing, runny nose, itchy or watery eyes, and itching of the nose or throat. It is often prescribed for seasonal allergic rhinitis (“hay fever”) and for chronic idiopathic urticaria (hives). Cetirizine works by blocking H₁ histamine receptors, preventing histamine from causing typical allergic responses. It is a second-generation antihistamine, which means it causes less drowsiness compared to first-generation antihistamines; however, some patients may still experience mild sedation or fatigue. It can be taken once daily, and is suitable for adults and children over 6 years of age (with adjusted dosing).

medicines.name: Losartan
medicines.description: Losartan is an antihypertensive medication that belongs to the class of Angiotensin II Receptor Blockers (ARBs). It is widely prescribed to treat high blood pressure, protect the kidneys in diabetic patients, and reduce the risk of stroke and heart failure.

medicines.name: Azithromycin
medicines.description: Azithromycin is a macrolide antibiotic used to treat various bacterial infections, including respiratory tract infections (e.g., pharyngitis, tonsillitis, bronchitis, pneumonia), skin and soft tissue infections, sexually transmitted infections (like chlamydia), and some ear infections. It works by binding to the 50S ribosomal subunit of susceptible bacteria, inhibiting protein synthesis and thus bacterial growth. A common dosing regimen is 250 mg once daily for three days (the “Z-Pack” course), but specific duration and dose may vary by indication. Azithromycin is favored for its convenient dosing schedule and relatively mild side effect profile. Common side effects include gastrointestinal upset (nausea, abdominal pain, diarrhea) and, less frequently, cardiac arrhythmias (QT prolongation), so caution is advised in patients with underlying heart conditions.

medicines.name: Albuterol
medicines.description: Albuterol (also known as Salbutamol) is a short-acting β₂-adrenergic agonist (SABA) used primarily for relief of bronchospasm in conditions such as asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). It works by stimulating β₂ receptors on bronchial smooth muscle, causing rapid relaxation (bronchodilation) and opening of the airways.

medicines.name: Bascupan
medicines.description:
Buscopan (Hyoscine Butylbromide) is a peripherally acting anticholinergic and antispasmodic drug used to relieve abdominal pain, cramps, and smooth muscle spasms of the gastrointestinal, biliary, or genitourinary tract.

It works by relaxing the muscles of the stomach, intestines, bladder, and uterus, making it effective in a variety of conditions involving spasm or cramping.

medicines.name: Lyrica
medicines.description:
Lyrica (Pregabalin) is used to control nerve pain, treat epileptic seizures, and relieve symptoms of anxiety disorders and fibromyalgia. It stabilizes overactive nerves by modulating calcium channels in the central nervous system.

It is not a typical painkiller—it works by reducing abnormal nerve signals, making it ideal for chronic nerve pain.

medicines.name: Panadol
medicines.description: Panadol is a widely used pain reliever and fever reducer. It contains Paracetamol (Acetaminophen) and is considered one of the safest first-line medications for headache, fever, body aches, cold/flu, and mild pain in all age groups, including children and pregnant women.

medicines.name: Aspirin
medicines.description: Aspirin (acetylsalicylic acid) is a widely used medication with two primary roles: as an analgesic and antipyretic (relieving pain and fever) at higher doses, and as an antiplatelet agent (preventing blood clots) at low doses.

medicines.name: Sharbat Faulad
medicines.description:
Sharbat Faulad is a well-known Unani and Ayurvedic herbal syrup used primarily to treat anemia (iron deficiency) and improve overall blood health.

It helps enhance liver and stomach function, increases the number of red blood cells, and helps overcome general weakness.

medicines.name: Clobetasol
medicines.description: Clobetasol is a very potent topical corticosteroid used to treat various inflammatory skin conditions. It helps reduce redness, swelling, itching, and discomfort caused by skin problems by suppressing immune responses and inflammation.

medicines.name: Brufen
medicines.description: Brufen (Ibuprofen) is a widely used pain reliever, fever reducer, and anti-inflammatory drug belonging to the NSAID class. It is commonly used for mild to moderate pain, inflammation, and fever.

medicines.name: Tilodol
medicines.description: Tilodol SR (Sandoz) is a prescription medication containing tramadol hydrochloride, an opioid analgesic used to manage moderate to severe pain in adults and adolescents over 12 years of age. It is available in prolonged-release tablet forms, such as Tilodol SR 100 mg, which release the active ingredient gradually over time to provide continuous pain relief.

medicines.name: Paracetamol 500mg
medicines.dosage: 500 mg tablet, take twice daily (every 4–6 hours as needed)
medicines.description: Used to reduce fever and relieve mild to moderate pain (e.g., headache, muscle aches). Generally safe for both children and adults.

medicines.name: Omeprazole 20mg
medicines.description: Used to treat stomach pain, gastric acid, and ulcers by reducing acid production.
